Roles & Responsibilities
Our client is a full-service brand-to-market agency that partners with clients across industries and markets to create fresh and innovative 360-degree marketing campaigns to meet their business goals. In addition to integrated marketing capabilities spanning the entire marketing communications spectrum, we also provide in-house video content and production capabilities They believe that inclusivity and diversity form the bedrock for the most innovative ideas, designs, and solutions.

Job Description
Aid management in implementing employment policies;
Arbitrate concerns and complicated interactions between employees;
Initiate recruitment efforts and plan new-hire orientations;
Coordinate HR projects, meetings, and training seminars;
Prepare reports and presentations for internal communications;
Update People Development SOPs;
Ad-hoc HR administrative duties.

Requirement
Excellent organizational and time management skills; Teamwork skills;
Familiar with labor laws;
Polytechnic diploma in Human Resources or related field;
Proven work experience as an HR administrative assistant is a plus;
Experience in recruitment marketing is a plus; Excellent written and communication skills.
